      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson iteration with arc-length control used for post-yield regime. Force residual norm at final increment: 3.2e-6. Energy balance error 0.04%. Solver error contribution to total uncertainty quantified as negligible (<0.1% of QoI uncertainty budget)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of simulation setup by analyst not involved in original model construction; documented checklist covering boundary conditions, material assignment, contact definitions, and load application.",
      "rationale": "Independent review performed by FDA OSEL analyst (not original model author). Checklist of 47 items completed; two minor discrepancies (incorrect initial contact offset in one sub-model) identified and corrected prior to final runs. Final model setup confirmed correct. Use error risk reduced to Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum plasticity (bilinear isotropic hardening) with frictional contact (mu=0.2) demonstrated adequate for compression-bending regime; alternative model forms evaluated and shown inferior or equivalent.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening material model with tangent modulus calibrated from tensile coupon data (Ti-6Al-4V, ASTM E8). Frictional contact at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces. Alternative model forms considered: (1) elastic-only — rejected, underestimates post-yield behavior by 18%; (2) kinematic hardening — equivalent performance, bilinear isotropic retained for simplicity. Model form uncertainty estimated at 3.1% of stiffness QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific coupon testing (E, sigma_y, sigma_u, n); geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of actual test articles; uncertainty bounds propagated via Monte Carlo (N=1000 samples).",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus E=114 GPa (CV=1.2%), yield strength 880 MPa (CV=2.8%), tangent modulus 2.1 GPa (CV=4.1%) from 12 tensile coupons per lot. CMM-measured geometry (rod diameter, screw shank diameter, block geometry) used directly. Monte Carlo propagation yielded combined input uncertainty of 4.7% on stiffness QoI, 5.3% on yield force QoI. Input uncertainty dominates total uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs from production lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to drawing tolerances; material certificates traceable to mill heat.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from three production lots. All components inspected by CMM; 100% conformance to drawing tolerances. Material certificates (mill test reports) available for all lots. Sample representativeness confirmed. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least two independent test conditions (e.g., displacement rates or fixture configurations) to assess sensitivity; environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) monitored and recorded.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single displacement rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717 protocol. Environmental conditions monitored (23±2°C, 50±10% RH). Only one test condition evaluated — rate sensitivity not characterized. This factor does not meet the required level (Gradation 2 required, Gradation 1 achieved). Noted as gap; risk accepted given quasi-static nature of loading and low strain-rate sensitivity of Ti-6Al-4V at room temperature."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA input parameters (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably matched to test article parameters; traceability matrix linking simulation inputs to measured test article properties documented.",
      "rationale": "Traceability matrix completed mapping 23 simulation input parameters to corresponding test article measurements or material certificates. Boundary condition equivalency confirmed: fixture compliance measured experimentally (stiffness 48 kN/mm) and replicated in FEA via spring elements. No unmatched parameters identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs; percentage difference < 10% for all QoIs; full load-displacement curve comparison via area metric.",
      "rationale": "Three scalar QoIs evaluated: stiffness (E/uval=0.87, diff=4.2%), yield force (E/uval=1.34, diff=6.1%), force at 40 mm (E/uval=1.81, diff=7.9%). All E/uval < 1.96 and all percentage differences < 10%. Area metric on full load-displacement curve: 0.031 (normalized). All acceptance criteria met. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to regulatory submission requirements and clinical failure modes; QoI selection justified by biomechanical rationale linking bench metrics to in vivo performance.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in FDA guidance for pedicle screw construct evaluation under ASTM F1717. Yield force maps to fatigue initiation risk; force at 40 mm maps to catastrophic failure mode. QoI relevance to COU confirmed by clinical literature and FDA guidance document (2014). Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activity geometry, material, loading, and boundary conditions match COU within documented similarity bounds; any differences assessed via sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Validation constructs are identical in geometry and material to the COU device (non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw, same rod diameter and material). Loading (ASTM F1717 compression-bending) directly matches COU. The only difference is laboratory environment versus in vivo; this is standard for bench-to-COU extrapolation under ASME V&V 40. Sensitivity analysis confirms < 2% change in QoIs for physiological temperature variation. Gradation 3 achieved."
    }
